    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix strict RX sample count assertions causing premature exits\n\n### Summary\nThe NR UE RX processing had overly strict assertions on the number of samples returned by trx_read_func(). In real hardware scenarios, slight variations in sample counts are normal but the current code would exit immediately when exact matches weren't achieved.\n\nThis change replaces the fatal assertions with warning logs that allow continued operation while still reporting anomalies.\n\n### Changes\n- `executables/nr-ue.c`: \n  - Replaced AssertFatal/DevAssert checks with conditional logging for sample count mismatches\n  - Added warning and error logging for trx_read_func() return value discrepancies\n  - Maintained execution flow instead of exiting on minor sample count variations\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Run OAI UE with real RF hardware\n2. Observe that slight timing variations cause sample count mismatches\n3. Previous code would exit with assertion failure\n4. With fix, warnings are logged but processing continues\n\nThe issue manifests as unexpected termination during normal operation when the RF hardware returns a number of samples that differs by even a few samples from the expected count.\n"
}